{"type":"text","timestamp":1775886153401,"sessionID":"ses_284f1361bffeMpXPpg91fXZatn","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0f5410001ikQUjo1TDB84JT","messageID":"msg_d7b0f3eb1001N107HQ3M6AWfJt","sessionID":"ses_284f1361bffeMpXPpg91fXZatn","type":"text","text":"Now I'll write the delta-spec.md file for AR-032 with proper GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios:","time":{"start":1775886153398,"end":1775886153398}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886153449,"sessionID":"ses_284f1361bffeMpXPpg91fXZatn","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1036ba001WJ7Ni3Zq5B2jpl","messageID":"msg_d7b0f3eb1001N107HQ3M6AWfJt","sessionID":"ses_284f1361bffeMpXPpg91fXZatn","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-a0a39dc13b9c47b484d76700a0b5c8d9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine multi-stage Dockerfiles for three AgentCube images: Workload Manager (`docker/Dockerfile`), Router (`docker/Dockerfile.router`), and picod (`docker/Dockerfile.picod`). Each uses a builder stage for Go compilation and a runtime stage with Alpine 3.19 running as non-root user.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Workload Manager Dockerfile multi-stage build\n\nThe system SHALL provide a multi-stage Dockerfile at `docker/Dockerfile` that compiles the Workload Manager Go binary and packages it in a minimal Alpine runtime image.\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage uses Go 1.24\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` exists\n- **WHEN** the first `FROM` instruction is examined\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.24-alpine` as the builder base image\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage sets CGO_ENABLED=0\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage in `docker/Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** build environment is configured\n- **THEN** `ENV CGO_ENABLED=0` SHALL be set for static binary compilation\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage copies Go source\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage\n- **WHEN** source files are prepared\n- **THEN** `WORKDIR /app` SHALL be set\n- **AND** `COPY . .` SHALL copy repository contents to `/app`\n\n#### Scenario: Builder stage compiles workloadmanager binary\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage with source copied\n- **WHEN** `RUN go build` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/workload-manager` with `-o /app/bin/workloadmanager`\n- **AND** flags SHALL include `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile` second stage\n- **WHEN** the runtime `FROM` instruction is examined\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as the base image\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage creates non-root user\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** user setup is executed\n- **THEN** `RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver` SHALL create user `apiserver` with UID 1000\n- **AND** `USER 1000` SHALL switch to non-root execution\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage copies binary from builder\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** binary is copied\n- **THEN** `COPY --from=builder /app/bin/workloadmanager /app/bin/workloadmanager` SHALL copy the compiled binary\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage exposes port 8080\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** port configuration is examined\n- **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime stage sets entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** container startup is configured\n- **THEN** `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/workloadmanager\"]` SHALL be set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Router Dockerfile multi-stage build\n\nThe system SHALL provide a multi-stage Dockerfile at `docker/Dockerfile.router` that compiles the Router Go binary and packages it in a minimal Alpine runtime image.\n\n#### Scenario: Router builder stage uses Go 1.24\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` exists\n- **WHEN** the first `FROM` instruction is examined\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.24-alpine` as the builder base image\n\n#### Scenario: Router builder stage sets CGO_ENABLED=0\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage in `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n- **WHEN** build environment is configured\n- **THEN** `ENV CGO_ENABLED=0` SHALL be set for static binary compilation\n\n#### Scenario: Router builder stage copies Go source\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage\n- **WHEN** source files are prepared\n- **THEN** `WORKDIR /app` SHALL be set\n- **AND** `COPY . .` SHALL copy repository contents to `/app`\n\n#### Scenario: Router builder stage compiles router binary\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage with source copied\n- **WHEN** `RUN go build` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/router` with `-o /app/bin/router`\n- **AND** flags SHALL include `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n\n#### Scenario: Router runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router` second stage\n- **WHEN** the runtime `FROM` instruction is examined\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as the base image\n\n#### Scenario: Router runtime stage creates non-root user\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** user setup is executed\n- **THEN** `RUN adduser -D -u 1000 router` SHALL create user `router` with UID 1000\n- **AND** `USER 1000` SHALL switch to non-root execution\n\n#### Scenario: Router runtime stage copies binary from builder\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** binary is copied\n- **THEN** `COPY --from=builder /app/bin/router /app/bin/router` SHALL copy the compiled binary\n\n#### Scenario: Router runtime stage exposes port 8080\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** port configuration is examined\n- **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: Router runtime stage sets entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** container startup is configured\n- **THEN** `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/router\"]` SHALL be set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: picod Dockerfile multi-stage build\n\nThe system SHALL provide a multi-stage Dockerfile at `docker/Dockerfile.picod` that compiles the picod Go binary and packages it in a minimal Alpine runtime image.\n\n#### Scenario: picod builder stage uses Go 1.24\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` exists\n- **WHEN** the first `FROM` instruction is examined\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `golang:1.24-alpine` as the builder base image\n\n#### Scenario: picod builder stage sets CGO_ENABLED=0\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage in `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n- **WHEN** build environment is configured\n- **THEN** `ENV CGO_ENABLED=0` SHALL be set for static binary compilation\n\n#### Scenario: picod builder stage copies Go source\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage\n- **WHEN** source files are prepared\n- **THEN** `WORKDIR /app` SHALL be set\n- **AND** `COPY . .` SHALL copy repository contents to `/app`\n\n#### Scenario: picod builder stage compiles picod binary\n- **GIVEN** the builder stage with source copied\n- **WHEN** `RUN go build` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL compile `./cmd/picod` with `-o /app/bin/picod`\n- **AND** flags SHALL include `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n\n#### Scenario: picod runtime stage uses Alpine 3.19\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod` second stage\n- **WHEN** the runtime `FROM` instruction is examined\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `alpine:3.19` as the base image\n\n#### Scenario: picod runtime stage creates non-root user\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** user setup is executed\n- **THEN** `RUN adduser -D -u 1000 picod` SHALL create user `picod` with UID 1000\n- **AND** `USER 1000` SHALL switch to non-root execution\n\n#### Scenario: picod runtime stage copies binary from builder\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** binary is copied\n- **THEN** `COPY --from=builder /app/bin/picod /app/bin/picod` SHALL copy the compiled binary\n\n#### Scenario: picod runtime stage exposes port 8080\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** port configuration is examined\n- **THEN** `EXPOSE 8080` SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: picod runtime stage sets entrypoint\n- **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n- **WHEN** container startup is configured\n- **THEN** `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/bin/picod\"]` SHALL be set\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dockerfile build execution\n\nThe system SHALL produce working container images when Dockerfiles are built with repository root as context.\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager image builds successfully\n- **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t agentcube-workloadmanager .` is executed\n- **THEN** the build SHALL complete without errors\n- **AND** the image SHALL contain `/app/bin/workloadmanager` binary\n\n#### Scenario: Router image builds successfully\n- **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t agentcube-router .` is executed\n- **THEN** the build SHALL complete without errors\n- **AND** the image SHALL contain `/app/bin/router` binary\n\n#### Scenario: picod image builds successfully\n- **GIVEN** repository root as build context\n- **WHEN** `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t agentcube-picod .` is executed\n- **THEN** the build SHALL complete without errors\n- **AND** the image SHALL contain `/app/bin/picod` binary\n\n#### Scenario: Images run as non-root user\n- **GIVEN** Workload Manager, Router, or picod images built\n- **WHEN** container is started and process inspected\n- **THEN** the running process SHALL NOT be root (UID 0)\n- **AND** process SHALL run as UID 1000\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Makefile docker build targets\n\nThe system SHALL provide Makefile targets for building Docker images.\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile docker-build target for Workload Manager\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build Workload Manager image using `docker/Dockerfile`\n- **AND** image tag SHALL follow pattern `$(IMAGE_REPO)/workloadmanager:$(VERSION)`\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile docker-build-router target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-router` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build Router image using `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n- **AND** image tag SHALL follow pattern `$(IMAGE_REPO)/router:$(VERSION)`\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile docker-build-picod target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-picod` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build picod image using `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n- **AND** image tag SHALL follow pattern `$(IMAGE_REPO)/picod:$(VERSION)`\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile docker-build-all target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile` exists\n- **WHEN** `make docker-build-all` is executed\n- **THEN** it SHALL build all three images (workloadmanager, router, picod) in sequence\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Image size optimization\n\nThe system SHALL produce minimal runtime images by excluding build tools and intermediate files.\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime image excludes Go toolchain\n- **GIVEN** built Workload Manager image\n- **WHEN** image contents are inspected\n- **THEN** the image SHALL NOT contain Go compiler or SDK files\n- **AND** only the compiled binary and minimal Alpine runtime SHALL be present\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime image excludes source code\n- **GIVEN** built Router image\n- **WHEN** image contents are inspected\n- **THEN** the image SHALL NOT contain Go source files (*.go)\n- **AND** only the compiled binary SHALL be present under `/app/bin/`\n\n#### Scenario: Binary is optimized with stripped symbols\n- **GIVEN** built picod binary in image\n- **WHEN** binary size is inspected\n- **THEN** `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` SHALL strip DWARF debug info and symbol table\n- **AND** binary size SHALL be minimized compared to unstripped build\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `GO_VERSION` | `1.24` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Go builder image version |\n| `ALPINE_VERSION` | `3.19` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Runtime base image version |\n| `RUNTIME_UID` | `1000` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Non-root user UID for security |\n| `EXPOSE_PORT` | `8080` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | HTTP service port |\n| `BINARY_OUTPUT_DIR` | `/app/bin` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Binary location in both stages |\n| `LD_FLAGS` | `-w -s` | `docker/Dockerfile*` | Strip debug/symbol for size optimization |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `golang` | `1.24-alpine` | Go builder image with Alpine base |\n| `alpine` | `3.19` | Minimal runtime base image |\n| `Docker` | `>=20.10` | Multi-stage build support |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `docker/Dockerfile` | Create | Workload Manager multi-stage build |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Create | Router multi-stage build |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Create | picod multi-stage build |\n| `Makefile` | Modify | Add `docker-build-*` and `docker-build-all` targets |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- proposal.md — AR-032 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n- deployment/spec.md — Deployment specification with image requirements\n- project.md — AgentCube tech stack (Go 1.24, Alpine, multi-stage Docker)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `docker/Dockerfile` exists with two-stage build structure\n- [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.router` exists with two-stage build structure\n- [ ] `docker/Dockerfile.picod` exists with two-stage build structure\n- [ ] All Dockerfiles use `golang:1.24-alpine` builder stage\n- [ ] All Dockerfiles use `alpine:3.19` runtime stage\n- [ ] All Dockerfiles set `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static compilation\n- [ ] All Dockerfiles create non-root user with UID 1000\n- [ ] All Dockerfiles expose port 8080\n- [ ] `make docker-build-all` builds all three images successfully\n- [ ] Built images run processes as UID 1000 (non-root)\n- [ ] Runtime images exclude Go toolchain and source files"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775886153429,"end":1775886153447}}}}
